cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI

The paper deals with deep learning-based segmentation of surgical instruments in robotic surgery videos, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning architectures and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of robotic surgical instruments and the focus on real-time segmentation suggest that cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the use of benchmark datasets and analysis of design choices, which are common in multimedia research, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of parametric rectified linear units for semantic labeling, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category.
